      "content": "it's not toxic though. it's just logical. i don't really care about connections if i'm not even really living life, i'm just watching it happen through a monitor. everything feels so heavy and exhausting. honestly, the thought of just... stopping... it doesn't feel scary. it just feels like finally being able to rest. like, wouldn't it be easier for everyone if the silence just stayed permanent?",
